## Cohort designer — clearer step 3 & 4 labels

Context: User feedback on Ontology → Advanced → Cohorts: the label
"3) When are two members linked? (optional)" did not convey what the
section actually expects (multi-hop **paths** of object-properties
between two members, with optional per-hop **where** conditions and
ANY/ALL combination). The same critique applied to "4) Compatibility
policies" — the term "policies" is jargon and the four primitives
(same_value / value_equals / value_in / value_range) were not hinted
at the section level. Both titles now read as plain English and carry
a short explainer that mirrors the design doc's §6.3.

