1. src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_cohorts.html
   - Step 3: title changed from "When are two members linked?" to
     "Link members via a shared entity"; added a `form-text small
     text-muted` paragraph below explaining the N-hop path model
     (with a concrete `Person → assignedTo → Project → governedBy →
     ComplianceType` example), per-hop `where` conditions, and the
     ANY/ALL combine semantics. Calls out that skipping the section
     treats every pair as linked.
   - Step 4: title changed from "Compatibility policies" to
     "Conditions every member must satisfy"; added a `form-text
     small text-muted` paragraph naming the four constraint shapes
     in plain English (same value of …, equal to, in any of, between
     min and max) and stating the empty default (every step-2
     instance qualifies).

