## Cohort designer — replace "class" terminology with "entity"

Context: Follow-up on the same Ontology → Advanced → Cohorts surface.
"Class" is the OWL/RDF technical term and confused business users who
think of the ontology as a graph of *entities*. The internal data
model still uses `class_uri` / `target_class` / `_classByUri` (RDF
field names that show up in the JSON contract and in REST routes —
renaming them would be a breaking change), but every user-facing
string in the cohort designer and the run page now says "entity".

Changes:

1. src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_cohorts.html
   - Section 2 label: "Group instances of class" → "Group instances of
     entity". Empty option in the dropdown: "— select a class —" →
     "— select an entity —".
2. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - `_populateClassSelect` placeholder option matches the template
     ("— select an entity —").
   - Save validation toast: "A label and a class are required." →
     "A label and an entity are required.".
   - Path-builder fallback root chip label: `'class?'` → `'entity?'`.
   - Per-hop `via` dropdown disabled hint: "pick previous class first"
     → "pick previous entity first".
   - Per-hop `target_class` dropdown empty option: "— class —" →
     "— entity —".
   - Terminal-hop tooltip on the `shared` badge: "…reach the same
     instance of this class" → "…of this entity".
   - Compatibility empty-state: "every member of the class is
     eligible." → "every member of the entity is eligible.".
   - Sample-values modal `metaLabel` for rule-level constraints:
     "on rule class" → "on rule entity".
   - `_pickSampleValue` guard: "Pick a target class and property
     first." → "Pick a target entity and property first.".
   - Trace explainer collapsing-on-target diagnostic: "The hop's
     target class URI…" → "The hop's target entity URI…".
   - Explain (Why?/Why not?) fallback reason: "Not in target class."
     → "Not in target entity.".

Note: Internal identifiers (`class_uri`, `target_class`,
`_classByUri`, the `/dtwin/cohorts/preview/class-stats` endpoint, the
`<code>target_class</code>` JSON-field hint in the trace diagnostic)
intentionally keep the RDF wording — they are part of the persistent
JSON contract and the public REST API.

