## Deployment — single source of truth (deploy.config.sh + app.yaml.template)

Context: User asked for one place to set every deployment value (app
names, DAB target, SQL warehouse, registry coords, Lakebase
project/branch/database, app.yaml runtime fallbacks) and run the
deployment from. Previously these were spread across `Makefile`,
`scripts/deploy.sh`, `scripts/bootstrap-app-permissions.sh`,
`scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh`, `databricks.yml`'s `variables:`
block, and `app.yaml`'s `env:` block — and the dev sandbox app name
was even inconsistent (`ontobricks-020` in databricks.yml + deploy.sh
+ Lakebase bootstrap defaults vs. `ontobricks-030` in the Makefile +
SP-perms bootstrap defaults), meaning `make bootstrap-perms` was
silently targeting a different app than `make deploy`.

This change consolidates everything into two new files plus a small
renderer, fixes the app-name drift, and turns `app.yaml` into a
generated artifact so it can never drift from the config again.

Changes:

1. scripts/deploy.config.sh (new, executable)
   - Single source of truth, sourced by `scripts/deploy.sh` and the
     Makefile `bootstrap-*` targets. Four sections:
     1. Apps: `APP_NAME` / `MCP_APP_NAME` + DAB resource keys.
     2. DAB target: `DAB_TARGET` (`dev` / `dev-lakebase`).
     3. DAB variable overrides: `WAREHOUSE_ID`,
        `REGISTRY_CATALOG/SCHEMA/VOLUME`,
        `LAKEBASE_PROJECT/BRANCH/DATABASE_RESOURCE_SEGMENT/REGISTRY_SCHEMA`
        and the `LAKEBASE_BOOTSTRAP_*` triplet for the psql GRANT
        script.
     4. App runtime fallbacks: `APP_*` variables templated into
        `app.yaml`. Default to the section-3 values where it makes
        sense (e.g. `APP_LAKEBASE_SCHEMA=${LAKEBASE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA}`).
   - Every variable uses `${VAR:-default}` so env overrides win.

2. app.yaml.template (new)
   - Copy of the previous `app.yaml` with `${VAR}` placeholders for
     every static value (warehouse fallback, catalog, schema,
     triplestore table, registry catalog/schema/volume, Lakebase
     schema, MLflow URI). Carries a "GENERATED FILE" banner so
     anyone editing it is steered to `deploy.config.sh` instead.

3. scripts/_render-app-yaml.py (new, executable)
   - Tiny stdlib-only renderer (`string.Template.substitute`, NOT
     `safe_substitute` — fail loudly on missing variables). Reads
     `app.yaml.template`, writes `app.yaml`. Called by `deploy.sh`
     before the bundle deploy and by `make render-app-yaml`.

4. .gitignore + git rm --cached app.yaml
   - `app.yaml` is now generated; only `app.yaml.template` is
     tracked. Added to `.gitignore` with a comment pointing at the
     renderer and config.

5. scripts/deploy.sh (refactored)
   - Step 0 sources `deploy.config.sh` (mandatory; missing config
     aborts the deploy).
   - Step 2 calls `python3 scripts/_render-app-yaml.py` to produce
     `app.yaml` from template + env (skippable via
     `--skip-app-yaml`).
   - DAB variable overrides composed from the config and passed to
     `databricks bundle validate/deploy/run` as `--var=` flags so
     `databricks.yml`'s `variables:` defaults stay declarative.
   - Resource keys (`APP_RESOURCE_KEY`, `MCP_APP_RESOURCE_KEY`) come
     from the config too — no more hard-coded literals.
   - Bootstrap steps export `APP_NAME` / `MCP_APP_NAME` and pass the
     `LAKEBASE_BOOTSTRAP_*` flags so sub-scripts inherit the same
     values without arg drift. New `--no-bootstrap` flag short-
     circuits steps 8 + 9 for partial deploys.
   - Header banner prints the resolved config (target, app, MCP app,
     registry path, Lakebase project) so the operator sees what's
     about to ship before validation runs.
   - Help text now points at `deploy.config.sh` as the place to edit.
   - Lakebase-target detection switched from `== "dev-lakebase"` to
     `== *lakebase*` so any future `*-lakebase` target inherits the
     GRANT bootstrap.

6. scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh
   - `INSTANCE` / `DATABASE` / `SCHEMA` defaults now read from env
     (`${INSTANCE:-…}` / etc.) so `deploy.sh` and `make
     bootstrap-lakebase` can drive them from `deploy.config.sh`.
   - Default APPS array reads `APP_NAME` / `MCP_APP_NAME` from env
     with `ontobricks-030` / `mcp-ontobricks` fallbacks.
   - Doc comments updated to reflect the new config-driven flow.

7. databricks.yml — app-name unification
   - Renamed `resources.apps.ontobricks_dev_app.name` from
     `ontobricks-020` → `ontobricks-030`. Same in
     `workspace.root_path` (`/.bundle/ontobricks-030/<target>`) and
     in three header/inline comments. The `variables:` block keeps
     its defaults — `deploy.sh` passes `--var=` overrides on top.

8. Makefile — slimmed down
   - Removed the `APP_NAME` make-variable (now lives in
     `deploy.config.sh`). The `deploy*` targets just call
     `scripts/deploy.sh` (no `-t` flag — DAB_TARGET comes from the
     config; only `deploy-volume` overrides to `-t dev` on the CLI).
   - Added `make render-app-yaml` for re-rendering without deploying.
   - `bootstrap-perms` and `bootstrap-lakebase` targets now source
     `$(CONFIG)` and let env vars drive the sub-scripts (no more
     hard-coded positional args).
   - `bundle-validate` composes `--var=` flags from the config so
     it validates with the actual deployment values.
   - `deploy-check` updated to verify `app.yaml.template` and
     `scripts/deploy.config.sh` exist (instead of `app.yaml`).
   - Help text reads `Edit values in: scripts/deploy.config.sh` so
     newcomers know where to go.

Modified files:
- .gitignore
- Makefile
- app.yaml (untracked; was committed, now gitignored — `git rm --cached`)
- app.yaml.template (new)
- databricks.yml
- scripts/_render-app-yaml.py (new)
- scripts/bootstrap-lakebase-perms.sh
- scripts/deploy.config.sh (new)
- scripts/deploy.sh

Tests: `uv run pytest -q` → 2023 passed in 65.97s.
