## scripts/deploy.config.sh — extract DEFAULT_* literals to a single block

Context: `scripts/deploy.config.sh` had every default value buried
inside its `export FOO="${FOO:-literal}"` line, which made scanning
the file for "what is this project's default warehouse / catalog /
Lakebase project" require reading through 80 lines of
section-by-section commentary. To change a default permanently you
also had to find the right line in the right section.

Refactor: collect every literal default into a new section 0
(`DEFAULT_*` plain assignments) at the top of the file. The exports
in sections 1-4 now follow a uniform shape:

  export FOO="${FOO:-$DEFAULT_FOO}"

This means: env-overridable wins, otherwise fall back to the section
0 default. The `DEFAULT_*` block is the single literal-value source.
Editing a default permanently is now a 1-line edit at the top of the
file; the export lines themselves carry only the conceptual
documentation (what the variable does, what consumes it).

Three "tracking" variables — `LAKEBASE_BOOTSTRAP_INSTANCE`,
`LAKEBASE_BOOTSTRAP_SCHEMA`, `APP_LAKEBASE_SCHEMA` — keep their
existing chained-default behaviour (they intentionally inherit from
`LAKEBASE_PROJECT` / `LAKEBASE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA`), so they reference
the live exported value rather than a `DEFAULT_*` literal. Comment
on each one explains the intent.

Verification: `bash -c '. ./scripts/deploy.config.sh && env'` before
vs. after produces the same 25 resolved values for every variable
the file exports (APP_*, MCP_*, DAB_TARGET, WAREHOUSE_ID,
REGISTRY_*, LAKEBASE_*, APP_REGISTRY_*, APP_LAKEBASE_SCHEMA,
APP_MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI, APP_TRIPLESTORE_TABLE,
APP_DATABRICKS_*, APP_SQL_WAREHOUSE_FALLBACK,
LAKEBASE_BOOTSTRAP_*). Env override path also verified:
`APP_NAME=ontobricks-040 bash -c '. ./scripts/deploy.config.sh
&& echo $APP_NAME'` → `ontobricks-040` (caller wins, defaults
ignored, exactly as before).

Changes:

1. scripts/deploy.config.sh
   - Add section 0 "Defaults" — 22 `DEFAULT_*` plain assignments
     (no `export`, no `:-` fallback) grouped to mirror sections 1-4
     for easy scanning.
   - Sections 1-4: replace literal defaults inside every export
     with `$DEFAULT_<NAME>` references.
   - Update header comment block:
     * Add section 0 to the section index.
     * Document the new "edit DEFAULT_* in section 0" workflow.
     * Update "To add a new variable" checklist (now 4 steps:
       `DEFAULT_NAME` line + matching `export` + optional
       `databricks.yml` `--var=` + optional `app.yaml.template`
       placeholder).
   - The three tracking exports (LAKEBASE_BOOTSTRAP_INSTANCE,
     LAKEBASE_BOOTSTRAP_SCHEMA, APP_LAKEBASE_SCHEMA) keep their
     `${VAR:-$OTHER_VAR}` chained-default form with an inline
     comment explaining why they don't use `DEFAULT_*`.

