## Cohort explain — robust class-URI matching across namespace drift

Context: Production bug reported on the `Consulting` domain — the
cohort preview produces sensible cohorts, but clicking **Explain
membership** on one of those member URIs returns:

> 'https://databricks-ontology.com/Consulting/Person/9' is not an
> instance of 'https://databricks-ontology.com/Consulting#Person' in
> the graph.

Root cause: `CohortBuilder._members_of_class` did a strict equality
check `t.object == rule.class_uri`. The codebase already documents
that R2RML and W3C-import paths normalise URIs into the *data*
namespace (`base_uri.rstrip('#') + '/'`), and properties were already
translated via `_to_data_uri`, but **class URIs on `rdf:type` triples
were assumed to keep the ontology form**. That assumption holds for
the `R2RMLGenerator` path (which preserves `rr:class` verbatim) but
not for the loader paths the user is on, where the rdf:type object
landed in data form (`…/Consulting/Person`). Consequence: the
explain view's class membership lookup silently missed every
candidate, even when the same rule's preview produced cohorts (the
preview path benefits from `_walk_path`'s lenient type-fallback,
which silently treats an empty type-index as "no filter" — the
membership check has no such fallback because it's a hard gate).

The fix mirrors how the engine already handles property URIs: at
lookup time, compare `rdf:type` objects against **every plausible
URI form** of the rule's class — ontology form, data form, and the
raw form as supplied. Same treatment for hop `target_class` lookups
in `_type_index_for_links` so multi-hop walks are equally robust.

Bonus: the "not in class" branch of `explain_membership` now emits
a diagnostic reason instead of the bare *not an instance* string —
it inspects the target subject in the loaded triples and reports
one of three precise failure modes: *typed as &lt;X&gt; not &lt;Y&gt;*,
*exists but has no rdf:type triple*, or *URI not seen in the graph*.
This turns the previously opaque message into actionable advice
("pick the matching class in step 2", "check your R2RML mapping",
"check the URI you pasted").

Frontend: `query-cohorts.js` `explain()` now syncs the form into
`this.rule` via `_collectFromForm()` before posting (mirrors what
`preview()` already does). Without this, an explain run right after
the user tweaked the form would post a stale rule and the new
diagnostic would describe a configuration the user no longer has on
screen.

Changes:

1. src/back/core/graph_analysis/CohortBuilder.py
   - Add `_to_ontology_uri(uri)` — inverse of `_to_data_uri`: rewrite
     a data-namespace URI back to ontology form using the configured
     `base_uri` separator (`#` if `base_uri` ends with `#`, `/`
     otherwise). Foreign and already-ontology URIs are returned as-is.
   - Add `_class_uri_variants(class_uri)` — returns the set
     `{class_uri, _to_data_uri(class_uri), _to_ontology_uri(class_uri)}`
     filtered to non-empty values. Single source of truth for the
     "every form a class might be stored under" lookup table.
   - `_members_of_class`: replace `t.object == class_uri` with
     `t.object in variants`. Behavior preserved when `base_uri` is
     unset (variants collapses to `{class_uri}` → exact match,
     matches the legacy semantics already covered by
     `test_no_base_uri_means_no_normalisation`).
   - `_type_index_for_links`: drop `@staticmethod`, build a reverse
     `variant -> {canonical class URIs}` map, route every
     `rdf:type` triple into every canonical bucket whose variant set
     contains the triple's object. Keeps the index keyed by the
     rule-side `target_class` so callers (`_walk_path`,
     `_trace_path`) need no change. Documented inline.
   - `explain_membership`: replace the bare "not an instance of"
     string with `_explain_missing_member`, which inspects the loaded
     triples for the target subject and emits one of three diagnostic
     branches: (a) **typed-as** — the target has rdf:type triples to
     a class set that doesn't include the rule's, report the actual
     types and tell the user to pick the matching class or fix the
     triples; (b) **untyped** — the target appears as a subject but
     has no rdf:type triple, tell the user cohort matching needs an
     explicit type and point at R2RML / loader; (c) **unknown URI**
     — the target was never seen as a subject, tell the user to
     check case / encoding / trailing slash and confirm Preview saw
     it.
   - Update the URI-namespace-normalisation header comment to call
     out the class-URI drift explicitly (was previously claiming
     "Class URIs are NOT translated" — true for the R2RML emitter,
     misleading for the broader loader landscape).

2. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - `explain()`: call `_collectFromForm()` (guarded by a
     `typeof === 'function'` and a sentinel-element existence check
     so a partial form doesn't crash) before serialising
     `this.rule` into the POST body. Mirrors `preview()`'s flow.
     The new diagnostic strings render fine in the existing
     `#cohortExplainResult .text-muted small` container — no CSS
     change needed.

3. tests/test_cohort_builder.py
   - `TestNamespaceDrift._drifted_graph_data_form_types`: new fixture
     mirroring the user's real-world graph — rdf:type triples,
     property predicates, and instance subject URIs all in data
     namespace (e.g. `…/Consulting/Person/Alice` typed as
     `…/Consulting/Person`).
   - `test_members_of_class_matches_data_form_rdf_type`: rule with
     `…#Person` resolves three members from data-form rdf:type
     triples — the regression test for the user's bug.
   - `test_members_of_class_matches_mixed_rdf_type`: a graph with
     both forms of rdf:type present resolves the union — guards
     against regressions in the variant set.
