## Cohort outputs modal — visible feedback for Auto-pick + Test write

Context: User feedback on Digital Twin → Cohorts → **Configure
outputs**: clicking **Auto-pick** or **Test write access** "doesn't
seem to have any effects (no messages back)". Both buttons were
swallowing every failure mode silently:

- `suggestUCTarget()`: `try { … } catch { /* noop */ }` plus an
  unconditional `data.catalog || ''` write into the input fields.
  When the API returned the OntoBricks error envelope (`{error,
  message, detail, request_id}` from
  :func:`shared.fastapi.error_handlers.register_exception_handlers`,
  e.g. 500 if no domain was loaded), `data.catalog` was `undefined`
  → the inputs got cleared to empty strings and no message was
  shown anywhere.
- `probeUCTarget()`: rendered `(data.checks || []).map(...).join('')`
  into `#cohortUCProbeResult`. When the API returned an error
  envelope (no `checks` array — e.g. `InfrastructureError(
  "Databricks credentials not configured")` → 500), the result was
  the empty string → the result div got wiped. The catch branch
  only fired on network errors (HTTP-level errors don't throw from
  `fetch`).

Both buttons therefore looked dead on every common failure path
(no Databricks client, no domain selected, server hiccup). The
fix turns each handler into a four-state state machine — *idle →
working → success | error* — with a visible state in every branch.

Changes:

1. src/front/static/query/js/query-cohorts.js
   - New `_renderProbeStatus(html)` / `_renderProbeWorking(label)` /
     `_renderProbeError(prefix, data, fallback)` helpers writing
     into the existing `#cohortUCProbeResult` div. The error helper
     understands the OntoBricks error envelope and surfaces both
     `message` (always) and `detail` (when present, in a small
     `<code>` block) so the user sees *why* the call failed, not
     just *that* it failed.
   - New `_ucFetch(url, init)` wrapper that always returns
     `{ok, status, data}`, parsing the JSON body even on non-2xx
     so the error envelope is available to the renderer.
   - `suggestUCTarget()` rewritten:
     * Renders a "Working…" line with a Bootstrap spinner before
       the request.
     * On success, fills the three input fields and renders
       a green "Picked `<fq>`" line with the backend-supplied
       `provenance` ("settings" / "metadata" / "registry" /
       "fallback"); also fires a success `_notify` toast.
     * On HTTP error or thrown network error, renders the error
       envelope inline AND fires an error toast.
   - `probeUCTarget()` rewritten:
     * Validates the three inputs before firing the request (was
       previously sending blanks to the backend, which then 5xx'd
       with a confusing message).
     * Working spinner with the resolved fully-qualified name
       being probed.
     * On success, renders a one-line headline (✅ "Write access
       looks good." / ❗ "Write access has issues — see below.")
       above the per-check rows that were already there.
     * Empty-`checks` edge case (server returned 200 + malformed
       envelope) now surfaces as a warning instead of a wiped div.
     * Toast for both success ("Write access OK") and the error /
       warning paths.

