     `_slug(r.label)`).
   - `save()`: validation now rejects labels that don't match
     `_isValidRuleName`, with a toast pointing at the camelCase
     example, in addition to the existing "label and entity required"
     check.
   - `_applyRuleFromAgent()`: agent-generated labels get camelized
     before being applied so the form starts in a valid state and the
     id stays consistent.
   - Removed `_slug()` (only call site was the now-replaced label hook
     + form collector).

2. src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_cohorts.html
   - Section 1 "Rule name" input: placeholder updated to
     `e.g. ExemptStaffingPool`. Added `pattern="[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9]*"`,
     `autocomplete="off"`, `spellcheck="false"`, and a `title` tooltip
     so the browser-native validation popup matches the JS message.
     Added a small `form-text` helper line under the input describing
     the format with a `<code>ExemptStaffingPool</code>` example.

Existing rules with non-camelCase labels are not auto-migrated — they
keep displaying as-is when loaded, and the validator only fires on
save. Editing such a rule will surface the camelCase requirement at
that point, which preserves backward compatibility for read-only
viewing.

